gomodel:SYNGO_5408  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 1: A series of synaptic biochemical fractions prepared from rat brain showed Gαq/11 (antibody that recognised GNAQ and GNA11) co-eluted in fractions with presynaptic marker proteins Munc-18 (STXBP1), synaptotagmin1 (SYT1), synapsin1 (SYN1), Bassoon (BSN). Various antibodies against G-proteins showed similar staining; Gαq, -Gαo, -Gαi and -Gβ (where the latter 2 were polyclonal/aspecific).\n\nFigure 6b, 7: pulldown of Gαq/11 within these biochemical fractions yields SYT1, SYN1, SNAP25 and Gβ (unknown which of GNB1-5). However, reverse-IP of synapsin did not yield Gαq while pulldown of Gβ did.. Experimental description: M&M: \"The rat brain specimens were fractionated by differential centrifugation, essentially as described previously\"\n\nantibody:\nanti-Gαq, -Gαo, -Gαi and -Gβ antibodies from Santa Cruz Biotechnology (Santa Cruz, CA, USA)" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" ;
        dc:date           "2023-03-15" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_5408" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .
